data.title: Juanfran, Koke and Raúl García, called by Del Bosque
data.meta_description: The national team will play on September 4th in Paris against France and on Monday 8th, in Valencia, against Macedonia. Raúl García makes his debut with the national team. Sául Ñíguez, is in the U-21.
data.text:
The national team will play on September 4th in Paris against France and on Monday 8th, in Valencia, against Macedonia. Raúl García makes his debut with the national team. Sául Ñíguez, is in the U-21.

The national coach Vicente del Bosque included Atléticos Juanfran Torres, Koke Resurreción and Raúl García in Spain’s squad-list for matches played on the 4th in Paris against France and on Monday 8th, in Valencia, against Macedonia, the latter is part of the preliminary qualifying round for France’s Euro 2016.

Juanfran and Koke return to the squad-list after the Brazil’s World Cup, while Raúl García attends the national team’s call for the first time, a reward for his effort and work.

This is the list provided by Vicente del Bosque:

Goalkeepers: Casillas (Real Madrid), De Gea (Manchester United) and Casilla (Espanyol).

Defenders: Sergio Ramos (Real Madrid), Carvajal (Real Madrid), Juanfran (Atlético), San José (Athletic), Albiol (Nápoles), Bartra (Barcelona), Jordi Alba (Barcelona) and Azpilicueta (Chelsea).

Midfielders: Busquets (Barcelona), Cazorla (Arsenal), Cesc (Chelsea), Iturraspe (Athletic), Pedro (Barcelona), Isco (Real Madrid), Silva (Manchester City), Iniesta (Barcelona) and Koke (Atlético).

Forwards: Raúl García (Atlético), Diego Costa (Chelsea) and Paco Alcácer (Valencia).

On the other hand, Saúl Ñíguez made the squad-list of Albert Celades, the U-21 national coach, a list where you can also find Javi Manquillo and Óliver Torres, loaned to Liverpool and Porto respectively, for the games against Hungary and Austria.
